sec.p:
The FEA model includes cover on the top and sides of the anode and bath in which part of the anode is submerged. The thermal, mechanical, and electrical properties of each material used for different analysis procedures were obtained from the public domain. As the inelastic behaviour of carbon anode material is difficult to find in the public literature, its mechanical behaviour has been assumed as elastic for the thermal–mechanical analysis. The following is the specification of material properties for each component:


stub and crossbar: similar to SAE1020;

steel weld: similar SAE1020;

aluminium anode rod: similar to Al6061;

aluminium weld: similar to Al4043;

transition joint includes three parts of material: Al4043, CP-Ti, and SAE1020;

thimble: cast iron (grey cast iron);

anode carbon: baked carbon material – special C;

cover: 50 per cent alumina + 50 per cent solid cryolite;

bath: molten cryolite.
